    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for LawDog offers a clear path to production, anchored by **Lawrence Butler**, who boasts our highest efficiency score of 72.92. Facing Leiter (xERA 4.43), **Lawrence Butler** benefits from a 10% park factor boost and a favorable platoon advantage, making him the cornerstone of our outfield. **Cal Raleigh** (69.89) is equally compelling; despite a moderate park factor, he draws a strong matchup against Buehler (xERA 5.19) and secures a critical +8% bump from hitting in the two-hole. Meanwhile, **Tyler Freeman** (67.69) remains an essential start against Weiss; the high xERA (7.36) of the opposing starter provides an ideal environment for **Tyler Freeman** to capitalize on his neutral platoon standing.\n\nWe are carefully monitoring the weather as we navigate our lineup construction. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (66.58) and **Taylor Ward** (54.52) are currently tagged with a 36% rain risk, which threatens to dampen their utility in a Roto format that demands daily volume. **Gleyber Torres** (62.92) and **Brendan Donovan** (66.36) are both set to capitalize on strong lineup placement and platoon edges, particularly **Brendan Donovan**, who thrives with a 14% boost against right-handed pitching. The decision to bench **Jung Hoo Lee** (45.03) was the most difficult; while his contact profile is solid, he ultimately fell short of our efficiency floor for the starting nine because he lacks the explosive upside needed to overcome the threat of Burns (xERA 2.76) today.\n\nConversely, we are exercising patience with lower-scored assets like **Yainer Diaz** (40.73) and **Luis Arraez** (48.27). While their scores are marginal, they remain in the lineup to protect our counting stats in a week where SB scarcity forces us to keep speed-oriented players like **Wenceel Perez** (51.46) active despite a tough matchup against Bubic. We continue to hold **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Bryson Stott**, **Jonathan Aranda**, **Masyn Winn**, and the currently inactive **Will Smith** in reserve, keeping a close eye on their platoon opportunities as the week progresses. **Drew Gilbert** and **Jeremiah Jackson** remain on the periphery, having failed to clear the 40.0 benchmark required to displace our current starters.",
